The paper discusses the use of algorithm diversity for improving the resilience of systems, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR). The paper also focuses on distributed algorithms and their implementation, which falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC). The use of metrics for measuring diversity and the evaluation of the proposed approach are related to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper proposes a synchronized execution algorithm for DistAlgo, which is a programming language for distributed algorithms, making the paper relevant to programming languages (cs.PL).
